New "Confluence Dashboard" Features:

Confluence Checkboxes: In the settings under Active Confirmations (Checkboxes), you can now individually enable or disable:
RSI/BB Extension: (RSI extreme + Price outside Bands).
Order Block Hit: (Price inside an unmitigated Swing OB).
CVD Divergence: (Cumulative Volume Delta divergence).
SFP Confirmation: (Swing Failure Pattern).

How the Logic Works: The strategy will always look for the baseline Multi-Asset Divergence (VIX, PCC, or COMP). However, it will only trigger an entry (and show a diamond) if EVERY box you have checked is also currently true.


Backtesting Flexibilty:
To see Both normal and confirmed signals: Uncheck all confirmation boxes. Every divergence will trade.

To see Strict confluences: Check the boxes for the layers you trust most (e.g., OB + CVD).
Optimized Performance: Fixed the syntax errors from the previous attempts and ensured all ta.* calculations (like ta.lowest for CVD) are performing globally to avoid backtesting inconsistencies.*


Visual Signal Levels:
Gold Diamond: The "Perfect Trade" — A divergence meeting all your checked confluences happening within a Nested HTF Order Block.
White Diamond: A divergence meeting all your checked confluences happening within a Current TF Order Block.
TP/SL Lines: Still visible during active trades to show you exactly where your targets are.
